ENTRY            G3146   20251202   20260508   20260508       G059
SUBENT        G3146001   20251202   20260508   20260508       G059
BIB                 16         35
TITLE      Photo-neutron reaction cross-sections of 59Co in the
           bremsstrahlung end-point energies of 65 and 75MeV
AUTHOR     (H.Naik, G.N.Kim, M.Zaman, W.Y.Jang, K.Kim, T.H.Nguyen,
            S.G.Shin, Y.U.Kye, M.H.Cho)
INSTITUTE  (3INDTRM,3KORKNU,3KORPUE)
REFERENCE  (J,EPJ/A,55,217,2019)
FACILITY   (LINAC,3KORPUE) Pohang Accelerator Laboratory (PAL)
INC-SOURCE (BRST) Pulsed electron beam on thin tungsten target
            (size 10 cm x 10 cm, thickness 0.1 mm)
SAMPLE     Co foil (size: 1.0 cm x 1.0 cm, weight of 10.35 mg and
            11.22 mg)
METHOD     (ACTIV) Irradiated for 1 hour with the bremsstrahlung
            end-point energies of 65 and 75 MeV (beam current of
            15 mA, 3.75 Hz, pulse length of 1.5 micro-sec)
           (GSPEC) Start after cooling for 9 hours
DETECTOR   (HPGE) Energy resolution of 1.8 keV FWHM at 1332.5
            keV peak of 60Co, and detection efficiency of 20% at
            1332.5 keV relative to a 7.6 cm diameter x 7.6 cm
            length NaI(Tl) detector
MONITOR    (13-AL-27(G,X)11-NA-24,,SIG,,BRA)
            - Al foil (purity > 99.99%, thickness: 0.025 mm)
DECAY-MON  (11-NA-24,14.959HR,DG,1368.63,1.00)
MONIT-REF  (,V.Di Napoli+,J,NCL,1,835,1971)
REL-REF    (R,,R.B.Firestone+,B,FIRESTONE,,,1999) WWW Version 2.0,
            Decay data
ERR-ANALYS (ERR-T) Total uncertainty                 (8.04-13.60%)
           (ERR-S,2.,10.) Statistical uncertainty          (2-10%)
           (ERR-1,6.35,8.04) photon flux              (6.35-8.04%)
           (ERR-2) conversion factor                       (2.65%)
           (ERR-3) irradiation time                        (~0.5%)
           (ERR-4) detection efficiency calibration          (~3%)
           (ERR-5) half-life and gamma-ray abundance         (~2%)
STATUS     (TABLE,,H.Naik+,J,ARI,156,108842,2020) Table 3
           (APRVD) Approved by G.N.Kim (2025-12-04)
HISTORY    (20251202C) S.C.Yang
ENDBIB              35
